I hope you liked this! Stay tuned for my PM routine 🤍

🤍Brides, save this to prep for your big day🤍

I often get asked by my clients what the best approach would be to prep their skin before their wedding. I have to say, planning is key! 

I always recommend having a laser treatment done no less than 6 months ahead of your big day. This allows time for your skin to recover and the treatment to take effect 

Using a gentle cleanser is so important because it allows your skin to be clean without stripping it of it’s natural oils

Having hydrated skin is key in ensuring your makeup will apply smoothly and last the entire day. While using the right serum is important, don’t forget to drink lots of water! 

You guys know I’m a big fan of wearing SPF. If you haven’t started using it yet, now is the time! 

Stay tuned for part 2!

Because the prep for the wedding is just as important as the wedding itself 🤍

Continuing from my last reel, here’s what you can do to prep your skin for your wedding: 

*1 Month Before* Have your last injectables appointment. That way any down time or adjustment period won’t impact your big day.

*1 Week Before* Get a hydrating facial & pause any retinoids or acids. Hydration is so important for makeup application, so a hydrating facial in addition to your daily moisturizing regimen can really help boost moisture. Also, retinoids and acids can irritate the skin, so I always recommend pausing or at least applying less in the week leading up to your wedding.

As always if you aren’t sure about your skincare regimen, especially leading up to your wedding, I recommend chatting with an expert like a dermatologist or esthetician to make sure you are set up for success.

How to get the perfect blowout — Part 1!
⭐️ Products below linked in my bio ⭐️

I’m so excited to share with you my favorite tips, tricks and products for achieving that perfect salon-style blowout. 

Step 1: Dry your hair with a microfiber towel. Removing moisture before breaking out the blowdryer is key to helping prevent heat damage, and the microfiber helps to minimize breakage! My favorite microfiber towel is from The Perfect Haircare Wrap. @theperfecthaircare 

Step 2: Always add leave-in conditioner! This helps protect your hair from the elements, while providing moisture, shine and smoothness. My favorite lately has been the Alterna Caviar Anti-Aging Replenishing Moisture CC Cream, which works into my hair beautifully and leaves it feeling super soft. @alternahaircare 

Step 3: Work the product through your hair beginning at the ends and working your way up to the root. For this step I always use The Wet Brush, which is great for detangling wet hair with less pan & damage. @thewetbrush 

Step 4: You’re almost ready to break out the blowdryer! Section off hair into pieces and secure the top with an alligator clip. When used correctly these can help hold up large sections of hair with no damage. @sharkbeauty 

Stay tuned for Part 2!

Get the perfect blowout, part 2! 

This time I’m using the Shark FlexStyle 😍 I love this tool and all the cool things you can do with it.

Step 1: bend the FlexStyle and attach the Styling Concentrator. Dry hair all around until it’s at least 75% dry.

Step 2: section off hair and secure with alligator clip

Step 3: straighten your FlexStyle and attach the Oval Brush 

Step 4: blow out each section, pulling it away from your head for easy volume 

*PRO TIP* adding a blast of cold air at the end of each section will help seal your style. 

Make sure to stay tuned for part 3 where I use the Auto-Wrap curlers to finish out this beautiful blowout!

The PERFECT blowout part 3! Follow @yourfacebygrace for more beauty tips & tricks. 

Here are the final tips on how to get the perfect blowout with the @sharkbeauty FlexStyle:

There are two barrel attachments with arrows on them. When curling, always make sure the arrows are pointing away from your face. 

Apply heat protectant with every layer. I love @kenraprofessional Working Spray. 

When curling, I recommend curling from the bottom of the strand going up — especially for those with long hair 💇‍♀️

Allow the hair to wrap around the barrel, and tug it a bit to secure. If I have time, I do a cold blast at the end of curling each strand to seal in the style. 

Release the curl and repeat this process all over the head! Don’t forget to switch barrels when moving to the other side.

When I’ve completed curling all around, I finally seal the look with @kenraprofessional Volume Spray, which gives my hair great body while keeping the curl. 

Thanks for following along! What style would you like to learn about next?

Paying a visit to my amazing friend @miamidermpro at her skin clinic @azalaskinclinic 
Paula is the only person I have trusted with my face since I started doing Botox with her 7 years ago. I refer all my clients to her and believe she is hands down the best injector in Miami. 
She also will always suggest the best and less abrasive way to address your concerns not just fill you with tons of fillers ( a miami special 😂)Less is more folks!

This time around my concern was that I felt my laugh lines were more pronounced than usual and I was feeling that I was losing a little firmness over all. I also wasn’t very happy with a few lines on my neck that show signs of aging. 

She suggested to start with a bit of Sculptra. 

Sculptra is NOT a filler. 
It’s a Biostimulating agent that stimulates your own collegen and elastin. Results gradually appear within weeks to a few months. 
Aside from sculptra, she added a little filler to my chin which has always been my area of concern. Naturally I have always had a very weak chin so for the past few years she has helped me have a snatched and more pronounce chin line 🫶🏻🫶🏻 

Be sure to book an appointment at Azala for any of your skin or face enhancing concerns 🫶🏻
